<!-- PAGE 5: READY-TO-SEND OUTREACH EMAIL (Instagram) -->
<!-- BUG 06 FIX: Content pillars used as content reference -->
<!-- BUG 07 FIX: LinkedIn guidance instead of fake email address -->
<div class="page">
    <div class="page-header">
        <span class="brand">Outreach Email</span>
        <span class="page-num">05 / 05</span>
    </div>
    
    <div class="content-body" style="margin-top: 0;">
        <h2 class="section-title">Ready-To-Send Pitch Email</h2>
        <p class="intro-text">
            Copy this pre-written pitch email. It incorporates your performance metrics and Groq-calibrated alignment logic, maximizing your chances of getting a response from the marketing lead.
        </p>
        
        <div class="email-container">
            <div class="email-meta">
                <!-- BUG 07 FIX: LinkedIn guidance instead of fake email -->
                <div class="email-meta-row">
                    <span class="email-meta-label">To:</span>
                    <span class="email-meta-value" style="color: #d97706; font-weight: 600; background: #fffbeb; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid #fde68a; font-size: 10px; line-height: 1.5;">
                        ⚠️ Find the Marketing Manager or Brand Partnerships lead for <strong>{{brandName}}</strong> on LinkedIn. Always contact a named person rather than a generic address like marketing@ or info@.
                    </span>
                </div>
                <div class="email-meta-row">
                    <span class="email-meta-label">Subject:</span>
                    <span class="email-meta-value subject">Collaboration: {{creatorName}} x {{brandName}} ({{totalFollowers}} followers / {{avgReelPlays}} Reel plays)</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="email-body">
                <p>Hi Team,</p>
                <p>
                    I've been following <strong>{{brandName}}</strong> and love the work you are doing in the space. I'm <strong>{{creatorName}}</strong>, and I create high-engagement Instagram content focused on <strong>{{niche}}</strong>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    {{aiParagraph}}
                </p>
                <!-- BUG 06 FIX: mostRecentContent from content pillars, not "my recent content" -->
                <p>
                    Based on my audience's interest in content like my recent Reel <strong>"{{mostRecentContent}}"</strong>, I believe a partnership would drive significant resonance.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Here's what I propose for a potential initial collaboration format:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Deliverable:</strong> {{deliverableStandard}}</li>
                    <li><strong>Audience Geo Focus:</strong> {{targetRegion}}</li>
                    <li><strong>Avg. Reels Plays:</strong> {{avgReelPlays}} plays ({{reachRatio}}% Reach-to-Follower Ratio)</li>
                    <li><strong>Audience Authenticity:</strong> {{authenticityScore}}/100 ({{authenticityLabel}})</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    I have attached my full verified SponsorScout Media Kit for your reference. Let me know if you would be open to a quick chat next week to discuss dates and details.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Best regards,<br>
                    <strong>{{creatorFirstName}}</strong>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="email-tip">
            <strong>💡 Tip for Outreach:</strong> Subject lines with specific numbers (views/plays) have up to a 60% higher open rate among busy B2B brand marketers. Customize the subject and greeting before hitting send. Always address a specific person by name.
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="page-footer">
        <span>Calibrated: {{currentDate}} — Data valid for 30 days. Re-generate after {{expiryDate}}.</span>
        <span>Generated securely by SponsorScout</span>
    </div>
</div>
